name: Issue 16
description:
Kissing 2013 goodbye with style.... Hell, we even have church windows in case you don't make to worship.... Plus, Chopper Dave's Steelshoe, Tom Fugle sit's down and talks to us and some pretty amazing bikes.... Still fighting the good fight and taking CHOPPER back... 


Issue 16 Features Chopper Wars, Blackboard Cafe Stripped Down, Out There with Lee Bender, Girl Bikes, Inner View with Josh Kurpius, Shoot with Josh Kurpius, Interview with Tom Fugle, Dosed with Rob Hulz aka Bobby Good Times, Below The Belt with Seabass, Class, Ass or Glass, Babes in Borrego, Flake The World with Erick Clay, Lady Parts with Mama Jen and Midwest Style.

Featured Bikes: Keg Killer's XS, Shotgun Shovel, Relampago Blanco, Turkey Vulture, Chromsexual, Hell's Belle, Tom Fugle's Plum Crazy, Ghost of Freedoms Passed, Chopper Daves' The Steel Shoe and Purple Reign.

name: Issue 15
description:
Another jam-packed issue.... VNM, Dan Collins Knuckle, the Snodgrass Bros. Inner View.... you know, lots of good shit.... we'll take the Pepsi challenge....

Issue 15 Features Danielle & Sevy, Strange Days 3, Zace Denim, Inner View with The Amazing Snodgrass Brothers, The Hood Bush, Masterangelo, 5th Annual Brooklyn Invitational, Girl Bikes, Dosed with Ryan and Jake of Volture, The VNM, Flake The World with Dave Nutton, and Lady Parts by Mama Jen.

Bike Features: Iron Haifley '69, Two Pan Dan's Pan, Voodoo Child, Shovelhead Jed, S.S. Deep Throat, Slim Forever Forever Shovelheads, Native Pan, No Knuckle-No Cry, Ramblin' Rose, Pinkie Pie, Golden Child, and Tamiami Knuck.

As always, thanks for the SUPPORT!

name: Issue 14
description:
We tried to jam 2 Issues into 1... half the mag is ALL Born Free 5 coverage... the other half is like a regular mag with coverage of ALL of the People's Champ bikes.... 

If you were there you can remember everything... if you missed either you can catch up..... either way we did our best to capture the events..... plus chicks, tech, music.... 

Issue 14 features a Centerfold of Edyn Bleir, Invited Born Free 5 Builder Bikes, Terry Shanks Custom Knives, Dosed with Tom from Windhand, and Flake The World with Robin.

Bike Features: Old STF Swinger, Atomic Power, David Chopperfield, Tuff Love, Ruby Red, PANgea, Special Edition, Locomotive Breath, Knuckle Sandwich, Union Made, People's Champ Winner the White Wizard, and the Imperial Pan.

What more could you want?

As ALWAYS.... THANKS for the support!
